<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6521&amp;p=28534#p28534"><![CDATA[
You can get old clock layout using the registry editor.<br /><br />Press Win+R and enter &quot;regedit&quot; and hit enter<br />Open the following key : <br />HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\ImmersiveShell<br />Click on the <strong>Immersiveshell</strong> folder on your left hand side. Following that, create a new <strong>DWORD (32-bit) Value</strong> in your right hand side. Name it <strong>UseWin32TrayClockExperience</strong>. By default, the value would be 0. You have to set the value to <strong>1</strong>. To change the value, double-click on UseWin32TrayClockExperience and enter <strong>1</strong> before saving your change.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14452">grisha22</a> — Fri Aug 12, 2016 4:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
